<br>
Also, NTOV is best done as a team thing.  I used to work it with two other monks.  We would all kinda share spotting and tossing and tagging duties.  It made for a very efficient and smooth raids, since we were always there for each other to make the pulls go well.  I've also done it single and with support from &quot;pull newbies&quot; and &quot;ego monks&quot; that wanted to do it all alone.  Really sucks compared to a nice solid pull team.<br>
<br>
BTW, the new tradeskills rates are great.  I spent 2K and over the weekend did: smithing 76, brewing 151, baking 135, and fishing 200.  Gonna knock off a bit o' pottery, push smithing to 162, then take tailoring to 250.  I don't think tailoring will go quite as quickly, but at least I'll be able to make all my own parts for halfling cultural when I get there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urubisthenome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rubis the Nome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 157<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/22/02 10:42:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3843.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hehe</span><hr size=1> Cool, I gave up smithing at 175 and helped a bud (who had 100k to waste) get his smithing into the 230s.  Came out with a suit of Fierce Heraldric and I'm happy with it.<br>
<br>
The Sks pulling thing is that we don't do NToV yet, just HoT (for coth mages before we start hunting for the rest of the guild on kael faction)  and the other monk pulls there, while anywhere else it might be the monk or a SK.  We usually have multiple SK pullers going in PoG, but that is the most notable zone we really chain pull multiple into the camp at a time on.  Our guild won't be seeing NToV anytime soon because, were the server roleplaying guild.  If we told anyone we did it they wouldn't believe us, we only have a dozen to two dozen members.<br>
<br>
Honestly our guild does really well for what they have to work with.  Competent folks but not alot of helping each other out.  Like you said about the monks helping make the pulls go well, we have a handful of officers that run everything.  It will be 1-3 people doing the entire raid and everyone else is just there.  Kinda depressing in that light but seriously we do much better than other guilds on our server twice our size. <p><p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=373025>Rubis<BR><img src=http://users.bigpond.net.au/stbt/sigs/rubissig.jpg></p></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwyrdup.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrd Up</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 649<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/22/02 11:34:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3843.topic&index=15>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> :)</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Kyrial walks into the room.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
